The signal is basically there so users can connect for updates in preperation for async path queries. Since this is not added now it is not so useful cause as soon as a user uses the query_path() function the result is updated.

If these objects are intended to stick around, maybe we should just have one of them to avoid confusion with the physics APIs (which look similar but don't work the same way).  It also simplifies the API by not requiring the user to keep two objects around and remember to always pair them with each other.

So, we'd have `NavigationPathQuery3D` which contains the properties of both `NavigationPathQueryParameters3D` and `NavigationPathQueryResult3D`.

Then you'd call it like:

``` gdscript
var query := NavigationPathQuery3D();

# fill in parameters...
query.target_location = Vector3(...);
query.current_location = self.global_position;

# run the query
NavigationServer3D.query_path(query);

# wait for the query to complete
await query.completed;

# get back the final path
var path = query.get_path();
