Unfortunately, just because an implementation supports one sample count, does not mean that they support all valid lesser sample counts (see [here](https://vulkan.gpuinfo.org/displaydevicelimit.php?name=framebufferColorSampleCounts&platform=all)). For example, it is common to support 4 MSAA samples but not 2. If a user requests 2 MSAA samples, but their device only supports 1 or 4, this line will return 2 and will still fail.

Instead I would do something like:
```
if (sample_count_flags & rasterization_sample_count[p_requested_sample_count]) {
    return rasterization_sample_count[p_requested_sample_count];
} else {
    VkSampleCountFlagBits sample_count = rasterization_sample_count[p_requested_sample_count];
    while (sample_count > VK_SAMPLE_COUNT_1_BIT) {
        //check each successively smaller sample count until you hit one sample
    }
}
```

